Wash and dry produce. Trim, peel, and grate @carrots{6%ounce} on the largest holes of a #box grater{}. Dice @tomato{1} into 1⁄2-inch pieces.

> TIP: If you added any other items to your meal (apps, sides, and/or dessert), you can get started on them now!

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}; cook, stirring, until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with @fry seasoning{1%tbsp}, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for panko over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{5-6%minutes} per side.

> TIP: If chicken is browning too quickly, reduce heat to medium and cover until cooked through.

Transfer to a #cutting board{}.

== Garlic Butter Bread ==

Place @butter{1%tbsp} in a second #small microwave-safe bowl{}. Cover with #plastic wrap{}; microwave until melted, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Stir in half the @garlic powder{1%tsp}, salt, and pepper.

Halve and toast @demi-baguette{1} in a #toaster{} or under a #broiler{}.

Brush as much garlic butter as you like onto cut sides of toasted baguette.

== Assembly ==

Thinly slice chicken crosswise.

Serve chicken, @mixed greens{4%ounce}, carrots, tomato, toasted panko, @Italian dressing{1.5%ounce}, @honey Dijon dressing{1.5%ounce}, and @Parmesan cheese{3%tbsp} family style and let everyone build their own plate. Serve with garlic bread on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.